<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-16082] Single choice() without otherwise() always executed</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-16082</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When building a route including a choice with a single &lt;tt&gt;when()&lt;/tt&gt; and without an &lt;tt&gt;otherwise()&lt;/tt&gt;, the first &lt;tt&gt;SimpleExpression&lt;/tt&gt;-&lt;tt&gt;when()&lt;/tt&gt; is always satisfied:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
from(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;direct:start&quot;&lt;/span&gt;)
    .choice()
        .when().simple(expression)
		       &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// always routed to
&lt;/span&gt;		       .to(whenTarget)
    .end()
    .to(end)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;An empty &lt;tt&gt;otherwise()&lt;/tt&gt; restores choice logic:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
from(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;direct:start&quot;&lt;/span&gt;)
    .choice()
        .when().simple(expression).to(whenTarget)
        .otherwise()
    .end()
    .to(end)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I included a simple Test-Case that &lt;b&gt;fails with Camel 3.7.x&lt;/b&gt; and &lt;b&gt;passes with Camel 3.6.x&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
